      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version controlled; regression tests documented for Ansys Mechanical release used in study.",
      "rationale": "All three modelling teams (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) operated under documented QMS environments with version-controlled solver releases and traceable regression test suites. Required gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark patch tests and manufactured-solution checks completed for linear-elastic solid elements.",
      "rationale": "Element formulation verified against NAFEMS benchmarks for linear-elastic solid and contact elements. Patch tests passed for all element types used in the pedicle screw assembly."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates < 5 % change in peak von Mises stress between penultimate and final mesh refinements.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw-rod interface region. Peak von Mises stress changed by 2.1 % between the medium and fine meshes, satisfying the < 5 % convergence criterion."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and moment residuals below 1e-4 relative tolerance; energy balance checked.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals converged to relative tolerance of 1e-5 for all load steps. Energy balance error remained below 0.3 % across the full loading protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent model review by second analyst; documented boundary-condition checklist completed.",
      "rationale": "Each modelling team conducted an independent peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions. A standardised checklist was signed off before result submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear-elastic constitutive model appropriate for metallic implant under sub-yield loading; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface slip.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V and stainless steel implant components remain within the elastic regime under ASTM F1717 loading. Penalty-based frictional contact (mu = 0.2) at screw-rod interface is consistent with literature and validated against experimental stick-slip observations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from ASTM standards and manufacturer certificates; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test specimens.",
      "rationale": "Young's modulus and Poisson's ratio for Ti-6Al-4V taken from ASTM F136 material certificates. Screw and rod geometry digitised from CMM data on the actual N=11 test specimens, reducing geometric uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N >= 10 specimens; specimens drawn from same manufacturing lot as simulated geometry.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens from the same manufacturing lot; lot traceability documented. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at the required credibility level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least two independent load configurations or displacement rates tested to characterise model sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single compressive displacement rate (5 mm/min) under one load configuration per ASTM F1717. Only one test condition was evaluated, which is below the required gradation 3. This is a known gap accepted by the assessment team given the prescriptive nature of the standard."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to physical test fixture constraints; loading point locations matched to within 0.5 mm.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry modelled from engineering drawings of the ASTM F1717 test frame. Loading point coordinates confirmed against CMM measurements. Boundary condition equivalency formally documented in the V&V plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E-value or MAPE) computed; prediction within experimental uncertainty band.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute percentage error between FEA-predicted and experimentally measured construct stiffness was 4.7 % across all eleven specimens and three modelling teams. All predictions fell within the 95 % confidence interval of the experimental distribution."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (construct stiffness, peak rod bending moment) directly correspond to regulatory submission endpoints.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak bending moment at failure are the primary endpoints required by FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. The selected QoIs map directly to these regulatory endpoints without surrogate substitution."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario geometry, material, and loading envelope encompass the intended submission scenario.",
      "rationale": "The validation construct (7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw, two-level ASTM F1717 configuration) is identical in geometry and material to the submission device. Loading envelope covers the full range of clinically relevant compressive-bending loads reported in the literature."
    }
  ],
